gemma2.reason: The text states that the Diocese of Udupi is a suffragan to the Archdiocese of Bangalore, meaning it is subordinate to the Archdiocese, not the other way around.  Additionally, the text refers to the Roman Catholic Diocese of Mangalore as having jurisdiction over the Udupi District prior to 2012.

llama3.1.reason: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Udupi was actually separated from the domain of the Diocese of Mangalore, making it a suffragan to the Archdiocese of Bangalore.

qwen2.5.reason: The Roman Catholic Diocese of Udupi was erected as a new diocese separate from the Diocese of Mangalore, making it a suffragan to the Archdiocese of Bangalore.
